import React from 'react'
import {
    ProjectsContainer,
    ProjectsTitleContainer,
    ProjectsTitle,
} from './ProjectsElements'

const Projects = () => {
    return (
        // check 2:34:20 for the id
        <ProjectsContainer>
            <ProjectsTitleContainer>
                <ProjectsTitle>My Projects</ProjectsTitle>
                <ProjectsWrapper>
                    <ProjectsCard>
                        <ProjectsIcon src={Icon1} />
                        <ProjectName>Hollywood Theater</ProjectName>
                        <ProjectDesc>A solo project which is a booking reservation app through Mongodb, Express.js, React.js, and Node.js for
backend, frontend, and middleware. Users can pick a movie and reserve their desired seats with or without an account. Users can also login and register, and registered accounts are able to view their purchased tickets and add Movies to their wishlist.</ProjectDesc> 
                    </ProjectsCard>
                </ProjectsWrapper>
            </ProjectsTitleContainer>
        </ProjectsContainer>
    )
}

export default Projects
